    <item>
      <title>Re: Veteran AA question</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=241552#M241552</link>
      <description>First, the "locked for two years" bit sounds like CS not understanding the question. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
What I believe they mean is: when you buy two years, you're credited&#xD;
for those two years in advance. Because of this, you won't increase&#xD;
anymore until those two years finish. Since you're credited with what&#xD;
you have paid for, you can't get more credit until you pay again, and&#xD;
you can't pay again until what you've already paid for expires.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
(and quite frankly, I wouldn't give much weight to what CS says. They&#xD;
aren't perfect, and they certainly don't know everything about the&#xD;
game. I give much more credit to the thought-out and researched&#xD;
comments posted by Kytherea and the Devs than any off-the-cuff comment&#xD;
by&#xD;
a CS rep. If nothing else, consider the CS rep you chat with has to&#xD;
respond right away off the top of his head. dev/halfling posts on the&#xD;
other hand are made with enough time for them to reasearch the facts&#xD;
before responding.)&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
As for the "problem" with folks who renewed in late May... I don't see&#xD;
that as much proof, or even suggestion, of any problem. The sticky post&#xD;
is quite clear they only update the veteran entitlements once a month.&#xD;
It doesn't say what day of the month. Until a full month has passed&#xD;
since the day you got charged for your renewal (and note I say the day&#xD;
you got charged, not the day you changed your options), you can't&#xD;
really claim there's a problem.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
For example, last week changed one of my accounts that was monthly to&#xD;
2-year. However, the existing month doesn't expire until June 28, 2006.&#xD;
I won't get billed for the 2 years until that date. At that point, I will&#xD;
be eligible for 2 more years of veteran rewards. However, it could take&#xD;
up to a month until I get it, because I don't know what day of the&#xD;
month they run the update on. If they run it on the 27th of every&#xD;
month, I'll have missed it by 1 day and have to wait until July 27th to&#xD;
get the update.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I think a lot of the confusion comes from players not realizing that&#xD;
this doesn't happen instantly or a few days after you change your&#xD;
subscription options. You need to pay attention to when your account is&#xD;
going to renew, and factor that, along with the monthly update, into&#xD;
your figuring about when you'll get your vet AA's.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
As for expecting acknowledgment from SOE.. Well, I wouldn't hold my&#xD;
breath. Unless you've got some solid evidence that it's not working as&#xD;
they claim here, I think you're going to be faced with them being tired&#xD;
of repeating themselves endlessly. Searching these forums there's a&#xD;
whole lot of threads just like this one. I can't speak for any Sony&#xD;
employees, but I know I'd get awfully tired of answering the same&#xD;
question over-and-over again despite there being a stickied post about&#xD;
it.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
If you've got solid proof of a CC being charged and 31 days elapsing&#xD;
without the account getting credited for the extra time, post it and&#xD;
give SOE hell about it. If you know someone who renewed in late May,&#xD;
check back with them in late June.. and when you do, ask em what day&#xD;
they got charged. (ie: make sure they aren't working from they day they&#xD;
changed their options.).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
