      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Your rewards are based on (A) the total of time you have &lt;U&gt;paid&lt;/U&gt; for previously and (B) the amount of time you have pre-purchased.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Taking a year off doesn't count to your total when you come back.&amp;nbsp; The free month people got when they first bought the game doesn't count. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If your character is 4 years old now, the only way you would get the 5th year Vet AA is to pre-pay far enough into the future&amp;nbsp;(like a 1-year plan) to make your account qualify for the 5th year.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For you, it would mean having paid for EQ through May 2007 at least. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The easy way to check is go into game and type /played, and it will tell you how many years you have credited to your account according to SoE calculations&amp;nbsp;(Mine is 7.4 years)&lt;/P&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Zacatac_BB on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;06-13-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;05:24 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
